UMUAHIA – The National Orientation Agency (NOA) Abia State Directorate will stage a roadshow today in the state to celebrate this year’s National Ordinance Day (NOD). The NOA Director in Umuahia, Mrs Ngozi Okechukwu who stated this in a statement at the weekend explained that the show was meant to honour and restore the dignity of “Our national flag and symbols which include national flag, national pledge and national anthem”. Besides, she explained further that honour also covers the country’s coat of arms, Nigerian constitution, Nigerian national identity card, the Nigerian passport, and Nigeria’s currency, saying that the citizens must demonstrate respect to these national symbols as “our pride and dignity”. According to her, the roadshow will start from the agency’s Secretariat at Finbarr’s Road to the major roads/streets of Umuahia, the Abia State capital.